---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
const lastUpdated = "March 22, 2026";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy - Dome"
  description="Privacy policy for Dome — local-first desktop app, optional Google OAuth, and third-party AI providers."
>
  <main class="legal-page">
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/" class="back-link">← Back to home</a>

      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="last-updated">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

      <div class="highlight-box">
        <strong>Summary:</strong> Dome is a <strong>local-first</strong> desktop
        application. Your projects, files, and settings are stored on your device by
        default. Dome does not operate a cloud service that receives your library
        when you use the app offline. If you turn on <strong>optional</strong>
        features—such as cloud AI providers, <strong>Google Drive</strong> or
        <strong>Google Calendar</strong> via OAuth, or
        <strong>opt-in analytics</strong>—data may be processed as described in the
        sections below.
      </div>

      <section>
        <h2>1. Data stored on your device</h2>
        <p>
          By default, content you create or import (notes, resources, attachments,
          settings, indexing data) is stored locally. The Dome project does
          <strong>not</strong> collect that content on its own servers.
        </p>
        <p>Typical local locations include:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>macOS:</strong> ~/Library/Application Support/dome/
          </li>
          <li><strong>Windows:</strong> %APPDATA%/dome/</li>
          <li><strong>Linux:</strong> ~/.config/dome/</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Exact folder names may vary slightly by install or platform updates; check
          in-app documentation if needed.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>2. Google services (OAuth)</h2>
        <p>
          If you <strong>choose</strong> to connect Google, Dome uses
          <strong>OAuth 2.0</strong> on your computer for specific optional
          features. You are always in control: you sign in with Google in the app,
          and you can disconnect in Settings.
        </p>

        <h3>Google Drive</h3>
        <p>
          Used so you can <strong>browse and import</strong> files you select from
          your Google Drive into your local Dome library. Dome uses industry-standard
          OAuth (including PKCE where applicable). Tokens and credentials for Google
          are stored <strong>locally</strong> on your device (for example in Dome’s
          local database). They are <strong>not</strong> routed through servers
          operated by the Dome project for authentication.
        </p>

        <h3>Google Calendar</h3>
        <p>
          Used if you enable calendar sync so Dome can read and manage calendar
          events you choose to sync, consistent with the permissions you grant.
          Tokens remain on your device unless you use other optional services that
          send data elsewhere as you configure them.
        </p>

        <p>
          Google’s use of data connected to your Google Account is governed by
          <a
            href="https://policies.google.com/privacy"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">Google’s Privacy Policy</a
          >. This policy does not replace Google’s terms or policies.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>3. Other optional third-party services</h2>
        <p>
          If you configure <strong>AI or cloud features</strong>, the application may
          send content (for example text from resources, chat messages, or indexing
          requests) to providers <strong>you</strong> enable, such as:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>OpenAI</strong> —
            <a href="https://openai.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
              >OpenAI privacy policy</a
            >
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Anthropic</strong> —
            <a
              href="https://www.anthropic.com/privacy"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer">Anthropic privacy policy</a
            >
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Google (Gemini and related APIs)</strong> when you add a Google
            API key or use Google as an AI provider —
            <a
              href="https://policies.google.com/privacy"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer">Google’s Privacy Policy</a
            >
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Other providers (for example Ollama locally, or additional integrations you
          add) follow the choices you make in Settings. <strong>API keys</strong> you
          enter are stored on your device and are not sent to the Dome project’s
          servers by the app for storage on our behalf.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>4. Indexing and search (PageIndex)</h2>
        <p>
          Dome uses a <strong>reasoning-based indexing</strong> pipeline (PageIndex)
          so resources can be searched and used with AI tools. Indexing data is
          stored locally (for example in SQLite alongside your library). Depending on
          your settings, the indexing step may call an AI provider you configure to
          process document text; that processing is subject to the provider’s policy
          and only occurs when you have set up that integration.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>5. Optional product analytics</h2>
        <p>
          Dome may offer <strong>opt-in</strong> product analytics (for example via
          PostHog) for feature usage or error reporting. If present, it is controlled
          in the app (for example under Settings → Privacy) and is off unless you
          enable it.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>6. Security</h2>
        <p>
          Because your primary data stays on your device, protecting your machine
          (password, disk encryption, OS updates) is important. When you use OAuth or
          cloud APIs, use strong account security on those providers as well.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>7. Your rights</h2>
        <p>You can:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Access and export data stored locally through the application</li>
          <li>Revoke Google or other integrations in Settings</li>
          <li>
            Remove local data by uninstalling the app and deleting its application
            data folder when appropriate
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>8. Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this page from time to time. The “Last updated” date at the
          top will change when we do. Continued use of the site or app after changes
          means you accept the updated policy where applicable.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>9. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For privacy-related questions: <a href="mailto:alder.velasquezobando@gmail.com"
            >alder.velasquezobando@gmail.com</a
          >
          or open an issue on the
          <a
            href="https://github.com/maxprain12/dome"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub repository</a
          >.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    padding: 6rem 0 4rem;
    min-height: calc(100vh - 300px);
  }
  .container {
    max-width: 800px;
  }
  .back-link {
    display: inline-flex;
    color: var(--accent-primary);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    transition: opacity var(--transition-fast);
  }
  .back-link:hover {
    opacity: 0.8;
  }
  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .last-updated {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .highlight-box {
    background: var(--bg-tertiary);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }
  .highlight-box strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }
  section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }
  h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }
  h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0 0.75rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }
  p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  ul {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }
  a {
    color: var(--accent-primary);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
</style>
